div.p:
The concerns of the Soul are Grace and Glory;

                  Solution. 

               holineſs here, and happineſs hereafter; a heaven here, and a heaven hereafter; a believing in Chriſt here, and a being with Chriſt hereafter; Grace here, and Glory hereafter, are undoubtedly the great concerns of the ſoul. But, to ſpeak to theſe diſtinctly.

1. A Diſciple of Chriſt,
               Sol. is under the teaching of Chriſt. As none teacheth like unto Chriſt; he is the Paragon, and Prince of Prophets;
               Eph. 4.21. ſo thoſe that are Chriſts, are under the teaching of Christ. But ye have not ſo learned Chriſt, if ſo be that ye have heard him, and have been taught by him, as the truth is in Jeſus.
